casebody.data:
John Doe et al. v. John Herrington (12217)

Speziale, C. J., Peters, Parskey, Grillo and Ment, Js.

Argued October 5 decision released October 25, 1983* Deborah S. Freeman, with whom were Abraham L. Clott, of the Illinois bar, and, on the brief, Martha Stone, for the plaintiffs. Francis J. Carino, chief court advocate, for the defendant.

The decision was announced from the bench on October 5, 1983.

 Per Curiam.

We find the record insufficient to afford a basis for an answer to the reserved questions.

The case is remanded to the Superior Court for trial.
